1
00:00:48,270 --> 00:00:50,110
I need you to do something for me.

2
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,310
You just...

3
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:56,010
have to go...

4
00:00:56,010 --> 00:00:59,450
back and forth so I can see you.

5
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:02,920
The thing you said you liked looking at...

6
00:01:03,890 --> 00:01:05,320
You don't mean...

7
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:06,690
Me?

8
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:11,830
I can't say exactly what this feeling is.

9
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:13,800
But...

10
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:19,100
I need you.

11
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:23,810
Can you stay?

12
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:57,910
Please stay.

13
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:04,850
(A Piece of Your Mind)

14
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,220
I have to stay.

15
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,130
So what? Why are you complaining to me?

16
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:22,970
Hey. I'll call you back in five minutes.

17
00:02:22,970 --> 00:02:24,330
Where are you going?

18
00:02:24,330 --> 00:02:26,470
- I need to go. - Look how you're dressed.

19
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,710
You're right. Not now.

20
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:35,480
Hey. Snap out of it.

21
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:40,620
Hey. Girls keep hitting on me like crazy lately.

22
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:43,950
That was a coworker just now that everyone says is pretty.

23
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:46,220
She calls when she's drunk and flirts like crazy.

24
00:02:46,220 --> 00:02:48,230
Why is this happening to me lately?

25
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:50,630
No one liked me in college.

26
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:51,860
That's right.

27
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:54,000
This is so disturbing.

28
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,400
Should I answer this or not?

29
00:02:55,530 --> 00:02:57,000
You say she's a coworker, so answer it.

30
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,470
If anything happens later, it's all your fault.

31
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,840
Then don't answer it.

32
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,840
Who was it, that you had to take it outside?

33
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:10,580
Well... So...

34
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:14,320
Seo Woo ran out like a crazy girl.

35
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,820
I stopped her and sent her home.

36
00:03:16,820 --> 00:03:19,220
What got into her in the middle of the night?

37
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,830
I should stay for him.

38
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,570
How do I do that?

39
00:03:40,340 --> 00:03:41,510
Seo Woo.

40
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,110
Seo Woo!

41
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,820
Han Seo Woo!

42
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:49,220
Seo Woo!

43
00:03:49,220 --> 00:03:50,520
Eun Joo.

44
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,060
Let me see.

45
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:56,860
Come over here.

46
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:01,430
Don't get any stupid ideas.

47
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:02,430
What do you mean?

48
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:04,500
I heard you ran around like a crazy girl.

49
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,840
I did not.

50
00:04:06,140 --> 00:04:08,410
Don't think about doing something rash again.

51
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,640
What?

52
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,450
I won't. Come on.

53
00:04:15,450 --> 00:04:18,680
I get so nervous this time of year, with your suicidal thoughts.

54
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,150
That's not it.

55
00:04:20,150 --> 00:04:21,750
I'm so sick of it.

56
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,550
Get your head on straight, got it?

57
00:05:23,650 --> 00:05:27,180
Seo Woo. A bunch of young kids came today,

58
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:29,490
taking pictures and traveling.

59
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,250
It looked nice.

60
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,590
You should date too.

61
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,840
I don't know where my own things are.

62
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,310
Should I bring it to you?

63
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:54,010
No, I'll go down.

64
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:58,920
Level B-3.

65
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,620
I'm here.

66
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,920
Go to C48.

67
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:51,770
I want to play this for you,

68
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:55,740
Mom,

69
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:58,340
Dad.

70
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:17,790
When will you be done with work?

71
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:19,060
(When will you be done with work?)

72
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,230
You're okay, right?

73
00:07:22,770 --> 00:07:25,000
I texted just because.

74
00:07:26,770 --> 00:07:29,910
"How are you? Isn't the weather nice?"

75
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:33,280
I like it when I get random texts like that.

76
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:36,410
I feel cared for.

77
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,950
I'm okay.

78
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:43,120
I just saw something I like looking at,

79
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,750
so I'm in a very good mood.

80
00:07:54,030 --> 00:07:55,500
I got my hopes up for nothing.

81
00:07:58,030 --> 00:08:00,640
I'm working on what to do to make it feel like...

82
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:02,140
I'm "staying" with you.

83
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:05,380
That's why I'm texting you for no reason.

84
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:10,350
Do you need anything right now?

85
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,780
(Before Dawn)

86
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:14,580
You usually have your head on the table when you're in the studio,

87
00:08:14,890 --> 00:08:16,120
so maybe a cushion?

88
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,120
Or slippers.

89
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:26,860
I'm sure you need something.

90
00:08:42,950 --> 00:08:44,080
I'm okay.

91
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:51,390
Guess what you often say like a habit.

92
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,290
A habit?

93
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,630
What is it?

94
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,300
"I want people to hear it."

95
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:05,540
Keep the door open so more people can hear it.

96
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,570
This is the last song we recorded here.

97
00:09:10,370 --> 00:09:12,410
"I want people to hear it."

98
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,940
I want to play this for you.

99
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:05,130
Mr. Kang.

100
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:08,570
About the house concert, I think it was booked a long time ago.

101
00:10:08,570 --> 00:10:11,300
- You remember, right? - I forgot about it.

102
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:13,240
I thought so.

103
00:10:13,470 --> 00:10:15,410
The rehearsal is today.

104
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:18,380
If you can't make it, let them know in advance.

105
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:21,540
Soon Ho, didn't you say you were a gardener?

106
00:10:21,850 --> 00:10:23,050
Yes, and I still am.

107
00:10:24,050 --> 00:10:25,480
How do you throw out plants?

108
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:27,050
Why are you throwing them out?

109
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:29,290
- Because they're dead. - I see.

110
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:31,390
Can you send me pictures of them?

111
00:10:31,390 --> 00:10:32,860
I'll check the state they're in.

112
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,690
(Mr. Kang)

113
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,000
Oh, gosh.

114
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,470
None of them are dead.

115
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,330
They're dead.

116
00:10:44,330 --> 00:10:46,170
If you can't keep them,

117
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:48,300
will you send them to my farm?

118
00:10:48,870 --> 00:10:51,110
- Are they in your balcony? - Yes.

119
00:10:51,270 --> 00:10:53,640
The eucalyptus is missing.

120
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,810
The one you bought for your wife that time.

121
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:57,580
Eucalyptus...

122
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:01,020
What does it look like again?

123
00:11:02,950 --> 00:11:05,360
We have the same one in our studio.

124
00:11:05,690 --> 00:11:07,120
Seo Woo got it as a gift.

125
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,960
It was neglected and almost died,

126
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,130
but I saved it. Hold on.

127
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:12,800
Who...

128
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,770
gave it to Seo Woo?

129
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:17,400
I didn't ask her.

130
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:28,310
Ji Soo went to the studio...

131
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,910
and gave the plant to Han Seo Woo.

132
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:39,020
(Moon Soon Ho)

133
00:11:40,290 --> 00:11:41,990
What's with the two of them?

134
00:11:47,730 --> 00:11:49,570
The weather is so nice.

135
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:51,770
I hate it.

136
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:40,620
She threw...

137
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:42,950
the plant away.

138
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:43,240
I want to play it for you.

139
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:06,530
(Gangwon Province Harmony with Nature)

140
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:11,900
(Express Bus Timetable)

141
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,880
As you can see, the buildings are still ablaze...

142
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,410
as if they had been bombed.

143
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,280
Do you want to go to your house with me?

144
00:15:22,580 --> 00:15:23,580
No.

145
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,350
I won't go.

146
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,520
I don't think I can.

147
00:15:38,490 --> 00:15:40,660
Is it like history taking?

148
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:41,660
It's different.

149
00:15:42,030 --> 00:15:43,570
You can ask more casually.

150
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:45,970
I can find its point of reaction right away.

151
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:47,540
Hold on.

152
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:57,410
Ms. Kim Min Jung.

153
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:00,920
I know you'll react right away...

154
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:03,050
if I talk about your daughter.

155
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,010
Where are you?

156
00:16:30,610 --> 00:16:31,780
You're where?

157
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:52,900
This is where I need to stay for you.

158
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:05,150
It's a huge improvement that you went to the bus terminal.

159
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:09,550
You said you hadn't gone since.

160
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:11,790
Right.

161
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,160
I can go with you.

162
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:19,960
It's okay.

163
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:24,330
I talked so big to my mom...

164
00:17:24,330 --> 00:17:26,340
that I'd bring her what I recorded.

165
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,370
She always asked me when I was going to,

166
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:32,310
saying she'd listen to it 1,000 times if I did.

167
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:35,040
Once my gift is ready,

168
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:38,310
I'll decide whether or not to go.

169
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:41,950
Let me hear what you recorded.

170
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,320
I'll pick the best one for you.

171
00:17:44,350 --> 00:17:45,960
Would you know if you heard?

172
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,620
You'll be shocked.

173
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:52,630
This one is...

174
00:18:01,940 --> 00:18:03,510
Brahms.

175
00:18:03,870 --> 00:18:05,440
"Cello Sonata..."

176
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:07,740
"Number Two."

177
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:12,110
- What's next? - Next one is...

178
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,640
It's not very good.

179
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:34,970
He's a great pianist,

180
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:37,170
but he's in a slump these days.

181
00:18:37,170 --> 00:18:40,310
He played this when he was slumping. You can tell?

182
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,380
I have no choice.

183
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,650
I'll have to show you my skills.

184
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,220
Do you play an instrument?

185
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:50,220
My mom was a piano teacher.

186
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:52,150
So you learned.

187
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:54,720
I told her that I liked listening, but hated playing,

188
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:56,130
so she didn't teach me.

189
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:58,630
I learned a little from watching, that's all.

190
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,700
Just wait and see.

191
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:03,200
I'll come with my recording gear next time.

192
00:19:04,730 --> 00:19:06,000
I can't wait.

193
00:19:20,780 --> 00:19:23,190
You look like you slept a bit,

194
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,520
or maybe not.

195
00:19:29,230 --> 00:19:31,090
Once everything is resolved,

196
00:19:31,660 --> 00:19:33,760
you'll be able to sleep.

197
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:36,630
Your body will send a signal.

198
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:41,970
"It's all good now. The complicated things are over."

199
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,510
Then you'll fall asleep.

200
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:48,440
Losing someone next to you.

201
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:50,750
It's tough every time you experience it.

202
00:19:52,980 --> 00:19:57,190
But if you have someone, you're bound to lose them.

203
00:19:58,290 --> 00:20:01,720
And you need a way to endure it each time.

204
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:07,600
What was your way?

205
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,030
Well, for me,

206
00:20:09,670 --> 00:20:12,800
I just needed one person who understood.

207
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:17,310
"I'm struggling. I'm lonely. Help me."

208
00:20:17,670 --> 00:20:21,040
The one person who would listen every time...

209
00:20:21,510 --> 00:20:23,180
if I tell them right away without hiding it.

210
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:25,250
Who was it until now?

211
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:26,680
Eun Joo.

212
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:31,790
But she's starting to get exhausted recently.

213
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:35,730
But then again, it's been a long time.

214
00:20:36,490 --> 00:20:37,830
One percent.

215
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,460
And one person.

216
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:43,930
That's all you need.

217
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:01,750
You left all your stuff at the studio.

218
00:21:02,990 --> 00:21:05,290
That's right. I only brought my phone.

219
00:21:05,290 --> 00:21:07,760
Let me go with you. I left something there too.

220
00:21:09,730 --> 00:21:12,400
Like your heart?

221
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:14,600
My bicycle.

222
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,970
Oh, I see.

223
00:21:21,370 --> 00:21:23,670
I'm slightly concerned...

224
00:21:23,670 --> 00:21:27,180
about what I should do to stay with you.

225
00:21:28,940 --> 00:21:30,780
How were the texts?

226
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:33,680
Did it make you feel like someone was with you?

227
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:35,080
It did for me.

228
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:38,950
It's not that I want someone physically next to me,

229
00:21:39,390 --> 00:21:41,290
but more like in the air around me,

230
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,460
warming my surroundings.

231
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,800
Your texts are effective.

232
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:50,600
That's good to hear.

233
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,540
I'll go inside then.

234
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:03,750
Bye.

235
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:07,850
- My bicycle. - Oh, right.

236
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,490
Your bicycle.

237
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,540
What's this?

238
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,750
What...

239
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:39,850
What are these?

240
00:22:48,990 --> 00:22:51,560
He is so silly.

241
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:55,560
They're pretty. I love them.

242
00:23:15,380 --> 00:23:17,720
Darn, he's so distracting.

243
00:23:18,950 --> 00:23:21,890
In Wook, will you let me work?

244
00:23:23,260 --> 00:23:24,760
I'll leave a little while later.

245
00:23:25,460 --> 00:23:27,600
I can stop thinking when I'm here.

246
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:29,900
I see. Stay here then.

247
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:31,370
Eat and sleep here.

248
00:23:31,370 --> 00:23:33,370
Don't think. That's the worst.

249
00:23:33,670 --> 00:23:34,870
They can make...

250
00:23:34,870 --> 00:23:37,840
your brain and heart rot away.

251
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:39,610
All right.

252
00:23:45,980 --> 00:23:47,220
Jin Moo.

253
00:23:48,780 --> 00:23:51,390
It's just a single plant,

254
00:23:56,860 --> 00:23:58,990
but I feel like I'm being laid bare.

255
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,930
(Eunjoo Homestay)

256
00:24:03,530 --> 00:24:04,570
Seo Woo.

257
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:07,140
I wasn't late yesterday.

258
00:24:07,140 --> 00:24:08,400
Open the door!

259
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,040
Hurry up.

260
00:24:10,310 --> 00:24:11,840
Take this.

261
00:24:12,780 --> 00:24:13,910
Gosh.

262
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:20,920
I'm so tired.

263
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,820
Hey, your face isn't covered.

264
00:24:28,890 --> 00:24:31,360
Cover it back. This memorial isn't for you.

265
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,660
Whatever, it's fine.

266
00:24:32,660 --> 00:24:36,330
No, cover it with something. Anything is fine.

267
00:24:36,730 --> 00:24:38,030
Do it already.

268
00:24:44,410 --> 00:24:47,410
There you go. Good job.

269
00:24:48,780 --> 00:24:50,050
Let's bow.

270
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:12,070
Ma'am, Seo Woo is staying in the semi-basement...

271
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:13,870
because she wants to.

272
00:25:14,140 --> 00:25:16,540
I just can't change her mind.

273
00:25:17,610 --> 00:25:21,980
So don't be disappointed in me.

274
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,550
It's good now.

275
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:30,190
If I don't say this, it makes me feel uneasy all year round.

276
00:25:34,260 --> 00:25:36,830
You aren't exhausted yet.

277
00:25:37,860 --> 00:25:39,130
What are you saying?

278
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:44,730
What about Chang Sup? Did he not come home again last night?

279
00:25:44,730 --> 00:25:47,370
No. I guess he's very busy.

280
